NUMBER 1218
NAME Below the Root
CAVE
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
MINEA
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Light dims swiftly only a few steps away from the opening, fading to a
soft glow tinging the curves of the massive roots twined everywhere. The
dusty air is warm and smells strongly of wood and rich, moist soil. Deep
shadows gather farther in, shrouding the passageway ahead in darkness.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1219
ITEM 0 72 ADJ1=210 ADJ2=264 VAL2=1215
; narrow rocky opening (leading out to Dark Heart of the Forest)
ITEM 1 1629 ADJ1=267 ADJ2=146 ADJ3=40
; rough gnarled brown roots
EXTEND 0 among the roots of an enormous tree
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Many of the rocks here have been shattered by time and the elements. One
especially large boulder has cracked down the center, split by a massive
tree root, revealing a crevice leading back to the surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The roots are twined so densely that virtually none of the dirt wall is
visible between them. They vary in width from the thickness of a man's
waist, to tiny rootlets that dangle and catch at hair and clothing. Some
of them seem to move on their own, but it could be a trick of the light.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You pick your way over the broken stones through the narrow opening.
   ECHO OTHERS %N picks %h way over the broken stones through the narrow opening.
   DISBAND
   MOVE 1215
   AFFECT 1215
   ECHO OTHERS %N arrives through the narrow opening.
   AFFECT 1218
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER It is said that the greatest of trees have branches that touch the sky and
      ECHO PLAYER roots that reach to the heart of the world. As deep as these seem to go,
      ECHO PLAYER perhaps the saying is more than a mere metaphor.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The root you are tugging on uncoils and shoves you away!
   ECHO OTHERS When %N tugged on the root, it uncoiled and shoved %i away!
   DISBAND
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 2 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You find yourself hurled back out the opening.
      MOVE 1215
      POSITION LAY
      AFFECT 1215
      ECHO OTHERS %N comes hurtling out the opening, propelled by an unseen force.
      AFFECT 1218
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You find yourself hurled further into the caves.
      MOVE 1219
      POSITION LAY
      AFFECT 1219
      ECHO OTHERS %N comes hurtling into the cave, propelled by an unseen force.
      AFFECT 1218
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFENTRY -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
  RANDOM CAVEIN 1 50 0
     IFVAR CAVEIN < 4
        DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 25 Several heavy rocks fall on you, dislodged by your passage.
        ECHO OTHERS Several heavy rocks fall on %N, dislodged by %h passage.
     ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1219
NAME Hoofprints
CAVE
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
MINEA
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Erratic gusts of wind whistle through the fallen stones, alternately warm
or cool depending on which direction the breeze happens to originate from.
The passage widens enough for a horse and rider to travel down comfortably. 
Perhaps someone has already done so, judging from the tracks in the soft
dirt floor, although surely no ordinary beast of burden left such prints.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 1218
EXIT E 1220
ITEM 0 302 ADJ2=91
; deep footprints
EXTEND 0 made by a large four-footed creature with cloven hooves
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The prints are deep where they appear in the soft sand around the water,
where perhaps whatever made them comes to drink. They appear to have been
made by a creature with very large, cloven hooves.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL 0
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Having seen the dark unicorns that guard Blackthorn Forest, you know that
      ECHO PLAYER these tracks can only have been made by one of them. Strange to find them
      ECHO PLAYER underground, but it implies that there is something down here they revere.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1220
NAME Prism Cavern
CAVE
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
MINEA
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The passageway opens out into a large cavern, its walls veined with shining
quartz. Jagged clumps of translucent natural glass jut from niches and cracks.
Stalactites of solid crystal pierce the ceiling, allowing in shafts of diffuse
illumination like the deck prisms of a sailing ship. Startling rainbows play
across every surface of the cavern as light touches the clear, faceted stones.
A trickle of water glitters as it flows down the eastern wall into a small,
deep pool.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1219
EXIT S 1221
ITEM 0 324 ADJ1=294 ADJ2=91
; small deep pool
EXTEND 0 worn into the stone by a tiny rivulet
ITEM 1 368 ADJ1=839 ADJ2=77
; transparent crystal stalactite
PUT 1 1502 ADJ1=331 ADJ2=56 ADJ3=251
; translucent clear quartz crystal (behind the stalactite)
; Yes, they can take it, but they can only get one per day since it's only restored at reboot.
ITEM 2 1062 ADJ1=56 ADJ2=77 VAL2=1220
; clear bright water
; Portal, not meant to enter. Used to capture the "drink" verb.
EXTEND 2 that smells faintly of minerals
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Over time, the patient flow of the water has worn away the softer
stone, leaving the bottom of the pool studded with tiny polished
gems. The effect is quite dazzling when light strikes the surface,
shimmering and refracting in a beautiful display of rich colors.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Tiny threads of darker quartz trace through the stalactite in hair-thin
lines of violet, pink, and smoky gold. Though it resembles glass, the
substance is as hard as any stone, and unlikely to be easily damaged.
The smaller crystals behind it, however, are probably much more fragile.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The water is cold and pure, as clear as flawless glass. The mineral
content is noticeable, but not overpowering, just enough to keep the
usual algae and minnows from taking up residence.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL 1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER You remember reading that stalactites and stalagmites are formed by
      ECHO PLAYER minerals deposited from water that seeps through the ground from above.
      ECHO PLAYER They usually are a mixture of materials, though, and subsequently an
      ECHO PLAYER opaque muddy gray or brown. You have never seen one of a pure crystal.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB TAP 1
   ECHO ALL The stalactite rings with a low, vibrating tone.
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL Other crystals in the room begin to hum in harmony, creating a brief eerie music.
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The sound fades away gradually into silence once again.
ENDIF
IFVERB THUMP 1
   ECHO ALL The jarring blow breaks loose many of the smaller crystals on the ceiling.
   DAMAGEALL SLASH 50 A hail of sharp fragments showers down on you!
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The pool is much too small for you to enter, and lined with sharp crystals.
   ECHO OTHERS %N starts to step into the pool, but then thinks better of it.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DRINK 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The water is cool and very refreshing.
   ECHO OTHERS %N leans down and takes a drink of the water from the pool.
   SPELL 515
   ; Agility III
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
ENDIF
IFENTRY -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
  RANDOM CAVEIN 1 50 0
     IFVAR CAVEIN < 4
     DAMAGEPLR SLASH 20 You bump against a razor sharp fragment of crystal, cutting yourself.
     ECHO OTHERS %N brushes against a razor sharp fragment of crystal, gashing %iself.
     ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1221
NAME Obsidian Bridge, West Side
CAVE
DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow arch of slick, black volcanic glass extends seamlessly out from
the side of a seemingly bottomless chasm. The ledge tapers off to either
side, into the vertical cliff walls that parallel the fissure. Strong,
erratic gusts of cool damp wind billow out of the chasm, ruffling hair
and clothing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1220
ITEM 0 61 ADJ1=210 ADJ2=297 ADJ3=218
; narrow smooth obsidian bridge (to Center of Bridge)
ITEM 1 331 ADJ1=348 ADJ2=87
; wide dark chasm
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
There are no railings or any kind, nor any irregularities in the glossy
surface to offer traction. The bridge is only wide enough for a single
person to cross at a time - if one of a group took a tumble, the rest
would surely follow. It is a mere handspan thick, seemingly too fragile
to support even its own weight.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Sheer stone walls, devoid of any handholds, fall away into utter darkness.
Empty space stretches ahead and below much farther than perception can
reach. A few bats flit by as though amused that someone cannot simply fly
across as they do.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB LISTEN -1
   ECHO PLAYER The faint sound of distant rushing water reaches your ears.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 0
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Although the material seems fairly normal, your familarity with basic
      ECHO PLAYER architecture tells you that this is no natural formation. Magic must
      ECHO PLAYER have gone into its creation, because even the most carefully set stone
      ECHO PLAYER must have some sort of seam left to show the crafting.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR AGI > 100
      ECHO PLAYER You watch your footing carefully as you step out onto the bridge.
      ECHO OTHERS %N carefully watches %h footing as %s steps out onto the bridge.
      DISBAND
      MOVE 1222
      AFFECT 1222
      ECHO OTHERS %N arrives from the western side of the bridge, walking cautiously.
      AFFECT 1221
   ENDIF
   IFVAR AGI < 101
      ECHO PLAYER You slip as you try to cross the bridge, falling into the chasm below!
      ECHO OTHERS %N slips as %s tries to cross the bridge, falling into the chasm below!
      DISBAND
      ECHO PLAYER You fall for what seems like forever, landing in icy water with a splash.
      MOVE 1235
      AFFECT 1235
      ECHO OTHERS %N is washed up into the chamber, coughing and spluttering.
      AFFECT 1221
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER It seems unlikely to you that any chasm could be truly bottomless, but
      ECHO PLAYER this one certainly comes as close to it as any you have seen. Judging
      ECHO PLAYER from the sheer walls, some sort of catastrophic geological event must
      ECHO PLAYER have happened to create a fissure of this size.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB JUMP -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You gather your courage... and fling yourself into the chasm!
   ECHO OTHERS %N strides over to the brink of the chasm... and jumps!
   DISBAND
   ECHO PLAYER You fall for what seems like forever, landing in icy water with a splash.
   MOVE 1235
   AFFECT 1235
   ECHO OTHERS %N is washed up into the chamber, coughing and spluttering.
   AFFECT 1221
ENDIF
