NUMBER 1235
NAME Submerged Chamber
UNDERSEA
DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This chamber is larger than it first appeared, and although the ceiling
is low, there is room for several people inside, waist deep in the cold
water. Long, slender plants sway in the gentle current. The subterranean
stream that flows into the lake has its source near here. A basalt ledge
has worn away into a dome overhead, where bubbles swept in by the water
have collected to form a large pocket of fresh air.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 914 ADJ1=274 ADJ2=379
; sandy crescent shore (to Underground Lake)
ITEM 1 1507 ADJ1=527 ADJ2=25 ADJ3=312
; domed black stone ledge
ITEM 2 694 ADJ1=183 ADJ2=833 ADJ3=345
; long slender water plant
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Glittering black sand marks the distant edge of the curved shoreline. The
waves lap against it in an eternal rhythm, barely visible from the chamber.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Light makes swirling patterns on the surface of the water, which are
mirrored on the wet black stone in a dappled shimmer. Delicate skeletons
of fossilized fish are imbedded here and there in the rock. Amidst the
moving reflections, they seem to swim - phantom fish in ghostly water.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The stems are long and supple, held upright by the water in which the
plant lives. It has long, delicate leaves that are almost white in color,
with only the barest tint of green.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY -1
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The air is cool and refreshing after the long swim.
   ECHO OTHERS %N breathes deeply in the cool air after the long swim.
   PLREVENT 40
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The air is getting a little stale. It is difficult to catch your breath.
   ECHO OTHERS %N seems to be having trouble catching %h breath.
   PLREVENT 40
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The walls seem to be closing in, and your vision is beginning to go gray.
   ECHO OTHERS %N is beginning to hyperventilate, and looks rather pale.
   PLREVENT 40
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER You pass out, unfortunately inhaling water instead of air when you fall.
   ECHO OTHERS %N sways and passes out. Sadly, %s cannot breathe water.
   DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 5000 You have drowned.
   POSITION LAY
   GMMSG %N just drowned in the Submerged Chamber. Unless the net locked up, it's %h own fault.
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The shore is too far away for you to reach from here.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   DISBAND
   ECHO PLAYER You take a deep breath and dive beneath the overhang, heading for the shore.
   ECHO OTHERS %N takes a deep breath and dives beneath the overhang, heading for the shore.
   MOVE 1225
   AFFECT 1225
   ECHO OTHERS %N swims to shore from somewhere near the bottom of the lake.
   AFFECT 1235
ENDIF
